import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  import { Playground, Props } from 'docz'
import Footer from '../Footer/Footer'
import styled from 'styled-components'
import { ThemeProvider } from '../ThemeContext'
import Typography from '../Typography/Typography'
import Flex from '../Flex/Flex'
import Container from '../Container/Container'

const layoutProps = {
  
};
export default class MDXContent extends React.Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props)
    this.layout = null
  }
  render() {
    const { components, ...props } = this.props

    return <MDXTag
             name="wrapper"
             
             components={components}>
<MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"footer"}}>{`Footer`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"properties"}}>{`Properties`}</MDXTag>
<Props of={Footer} />
<Playground __position={1} __code={'<ThemeProvider>\n  <Footer />\n</ThemeProvider>'} __scope={{props: this ? this.props : props,Playground,Props,Footer,styled,ThemeProvider,Typography,Flex,Container}} __codesandbox={`undefined`}>
  <ThemeProvider>
      <Footer>
  </Footer>
    </ThemeProvider>
</Playground>
           </MDXTag>
  }
}
MDXContent.isMDXComponent = true
